 war continuing for a further two years. It sets the battle and campaign in the wider context of a war which included action in the West Indies, Europe, Africa, Asia, and at sea; shows how movements of theFrench and British navies were a crucial factor; and, overall, reassesses the causes and significance of the battle. JOHN D. GRAINGER, a former school-teacher, is the author of numerous books on military history, rangingfrom the Roman period to the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMilitary planningxHistoryy18th centuryzVirginiazYorktown. 0aStrategyxHistoryy18th century. 4aEighteenth Century Studies. 4aMilitary History. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Military / General.2bisacsh  aAlexander Hamilton.  aHamilton.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846153716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846153716/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles